issue.title: Support binding `retries` on `zeebe:taskDefinition` through element template

labels.name: spring cleaning
labels.description: Could be cleaned up one day

labels.name: Camunda Cloud
labels.description: Flags an issue as related to Camunda 8

milestone.title: M70
milestone.description: Tracks the `v5.17.0` release of the app.

issue.body:
_This is a child of https://github.com/camunda/product-hub/issues/1382._


__Is your feature request related to a problem? Please describe.__

When trying to create services tasks templates we only can bind the type via `zeebe:taskDefinition:type` but we can't bind retries elements.

__Describe the solution you'd like__

Add new binding: `zeebe:taskDefinition` which accepts `property` as the name of the templated property. This can be `type` or `retries` but ready for new properties.

* [ ] Implement in JSON schema
* [ ] Implement in bpmn-js-element-templates
* [ ] Remove obsolete `zeebe:taskDefinition:retries` from JSON schema as never implemented

__Describe alternatives you've considered__

We unlink after selecting templates to be able to set retries.

----

Also mentioned via [slack](https://camunda.slack.com/archives/CKGH9LR40/p1677510188850949).

comment.body: I've sketched a solution together with @philippfromme, and added task list to the first comment in the issue.

issue.title: Allow defining a custom default diagram.bpmn file
issue.body:
### Problem you would like to solve

When I select File > New BPMN Diagram, the following process appears with 4 linting errors. 

![image](https://github.com/camunda/camunda-modeler/assets/584225/98812240-13ff-4955-9653-b18a29d0ef71)

This appears to be picking from this path: client/src/app/tabs/bpmn/diagram.bpmn

It seems like a great idea to allow a modeler to customize his/her default bpmn starter diagram.

This opens up endless possibilities such as defining custom extension properties on all models, 

### Proposed solution

Make this diagram.bpmn customizable by placing it on resources directory. If one exists, the modeler takes it otherwise the default one 

### Alternatives considered

None

### Additional context

_No response_

comment.body:
Hi, thanks for creating this issue. 
I think it's a valid feature request, even though we may not want invest in it right now.
Potential problems to solve:
* How to inject the execution platform? Currently we do it via simple template mechanism (`{{ }}`). Can we enforce it on the user?
* What should we do if provided diagram is broken? Perhaps we'd need to perform some form of validation here.

issue.title: Allow HTML in Element Templates Description
issue.body:
### Problem you would like to solve

Looking for a way to link to external documentation sites for element templates.

Right now, hyperlinks are allowed on input and output description but not the actual template itself. 

See below, how the link appears, in the element template description. It is not allowing hyperlinks.
![image](https://github.com/camunda/camunda-modeler/assets/584225/0871a20d-48ca-40ef-8638-ee26a517add0)

But check out this input parameter, here it allows hyperlinks. 
![image](https://github.com/camunda/camunda-modeler/assets/584225/ab05cdcd-dfa6-434a-a152-78182952d3ad)


### Proposed solution

Allow hyperlinks on Template Description, just like input and output does. 

### Alternatives considered

There are no alternatives to do this, except defining at each input level. 

### Additional context

We are on Camunda 7, but this may help all users on 7 & 8 versions.

issue.title: Support FEEL for fields' default value

labels.name: spring cleaning
labels.description: Could be cleaned up one day

issue.body: ### Problem you would like to solve Currently, the default value of various fields (Number, Datetime, Text field, Text area, Checkbox, Radio, ...) can only be a static value. I'd like this to be a FEEL expression so that this can be dynamic, e.g. based on process variables. ### Proposed solution It would be great if the default value could be switched between a static text and a FEEL expression. This would be similar to other properties, e.g. Label, Field Description, ... ### Alternatives considered I'm not aware of an alternate solution or workaround. ### Additional context I'd like to see this for C8 - I'm not sure if this could also be applied to C7 forms. It could look like this: (note I added the blue "fx"): And when "fx" is clicked it looks like all other fields which allow FEEL expressions:
